A lecturer with Christian University of Mkar, Mkar, Gboko (UMM) Mr Moses Tarnongu, who died in a ghastly motor accident alongside his ,wife and three kids were buried Tuesday. The burial was held in his home town Anyamor, Ikyase village, Gboko local government area in Benue state. The entire Tarnongo family were killed when a trailer lost control and ran over their Toyota car which was parked at a police check point along Ugbema- Ushongo federal highway on October 10th in Benue state. Hundreds of mourners turned out for the burial. Many of the sympathizers wept profusely as the four caskets containing the bodies of the Tarnongo family were lowered into their graves .